		<h4>Cloud Hosting</h4>
		<p>This term is actually a contradiction, since in the Cloud there is no hosting. You purchase "pipeline" instead of space, pay for what you use.</p>
		
		<p>The main system and database is a service provided by Salesforce.com, which also includes the Administrative Interface like listings, reports, dashboards , etc</p>

		<p>Each web and mobile application along with API Integration Hubs is hosted on Heroku, a Salesforce.com company that revolutionized the Open Source Community by providing an extremely efficient , scalable and affordable platform to deploy applications in seconds. </p>
    
    
		<p>The code , organized , tested and object oriented is stored in separated repositories; Also in the cloud allowing distributed teams to work on the same projects with out conflicts with 100% reliability.</p>

